chassisId.name: chassisId
chassisId.description: The unique identifier assigned to this station during manufacturing.

chassisType.name: chassisType
chassisType.description: The type of the LinkBuilder 3GH chassis.

chassisRevision.name: chassisRevision
chassisRevision.description: The revision number of this chassis.

chassisName.name: chassisName
chassisName.description: The text string describing this chassis.

chassisNameAbbrev.name: chassisNameAbbrev
chassisNameAbbrev.description: The text string describing the generic name for this chassis.

chassisManufacturer.name: chassisManufacturer
chassisManufacturer.description: The text string describing the manufacturer of this chassis.

chassisSlotCount.name: chassisSlotCount
chassisSlotCount.description: The number of slots in this chassis.

chassisBuildTime.name: chassisBuildTime
chassisBuildTime.description: The build time of the LinkBuilder 3GH system software.

chassisSoftwareRevision.name: chassisSoftwareRevision
chassisSoftwareRevision.description: The revision number of the LinkBuilder 3GH system software.

chassisControlPanelColumns.name: chassisControlPanelColumns
chassisControlPanelColumns.description: The number of columns in the control panel display.

chassisControlPanelLines.name: chassisControlPanelLines
chassisControlPanelLines.description: The number of lines in the control panel display.

chassisControlPanelText.name: chassisControlPanelText
chassisControlPanelText.description: The text currently displayed in the control panel display.

chassisAction.name: chassisAction
chassisAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). The result of setting this object to each acceptable value is: reset: resets the LinkBuilder 3GH system.

slotTable.name: slotTable
slotTable.description: A list of slot entries. A single instance of this object exists for each slot in the LinkBuilder 3GH chassis.

slotEntry.name: slotEntry
slotEntry.description: A slot entry contains information common to a specified slot within a LinkBuilder 3GH system.

slotIndex.name: slotIndex
slotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this slot within the LinkBuilder 3GH chassis.

slotBoardType.name: slotBoardType
slotBoardType.description: The type of board residing in this slot.

slotBoardRevision.name: slotBoardRevision
slotBoardRevision.description: The revision number of the board in this slot.

slotBoardStatus.name: slotBoardStatus
slotBoardStatus.description: The status of the board in this slot.

slotBoardName.name: slotBoardName
slotBoardName.description: The text string describing this board type.

slotBoardNameAbbrev.name: slotBoardNameAbbrev
slotBoardNameAbbrev.description: The abbreviation describing this board type.

slotBoardAction.name: slotBoardAction
slotBoardAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). The result of setting this object to each acceptable value is: runDiagnostics: runs the board's offline diagnostics.

smmTable.name: smmTable
smmTable.description: A list of System Management Module (SMM) entries. An entry exists for each Slot Table Entry whose board type is SMM. This table is indexed by the physical slot number of this SMM within the LinkBuilder 3GH chassis. The entries need not have consecutive slot indices. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lb3gh MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available via the lbSlot table.

smmEntry.name: smmEntry
smmEntry.description: An SMM entry contains information common to a single System Management Module (SMM) within a LinkBuilder 3GH system.

smmSlotIndex.name: smmSlotIndex
smmSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this slot within the LinkBuilder 3GH chassis.

smmEthernetPortCount.name: smmEthernetPortCount
smmEthernetPortCount.description: The number of Ethernet ports on this board.

smmBaseEthernetPortIndex.name: smmBaseEthernetPortIndex
smmBaseEthernetPortIndex.description: The system-wide index for the first Ethernet port on this board.

fbcmTable.name: fbcmTable
fbcmTable.description: A list of FDDI Backbone Connectivity Module (FBCM) entries. An entry exists for each Slot Table Entry whose board type is FBCM. This table is indexed by the physical slot number of this FBCM within the LinkBuilder 3GH chassis. The entries need not have consecutive slot indices. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lb3gh MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available via the lbSlot table.

fbcmEntry.name: fbcmEntry
fbcmEntry.description: An FBCM entry contains information common to a single FDDI Backbone Connectivity Module (FBCM) within a LinkBuilder 3GH system.

fbcmSlotIndex.name: fbcmSlotIndex
fbcmSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this slot within the LinkBuilder 3GH chassis.

fbcmMACCount.name: fbcmMACCount
fbcmMACCount.description: The number of FDDI MACs present on this board.

fbcmBaseMACIndex.name: fbcmBaseMACIndex
fbcmBaseMACIndex.description: The system-wide index of the first FDDI MAC on this board. Additional MACs on this board will have consecutively increasing MAC indices following this index.

fbcmPortCount.name: fbcmPortCount
fbcmPortCount.description: The number of FDDI ports present on this board.

fbcmBasePortIndex.name: fbcmBasePortIndex
fbcmBasePortIndex.description: The system-wide index of the first FDDI port on this board. Additional ports on this board will have consecutively increasing port indices following this index.

fcmTable.name: fcmTable
fcmTable.description: A list of FDDI Concentrator Module (FCM) entries. An entry exists for each Slot Table Entry whose board type is FCM. This table is indexed by the physical slot number of this FCM within the LinkBuilder 3GH chassis. The entries need not have consecutive slot indices. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lb3gh MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available via the lbSlot table.

fcmEntry.name: fcmEntry
fcmEntry.description: An FCM entry contains information common to a single FDDI Concentrator Module (FCM) within a LinkBuilder 3GH system.

fcmSlotIndex.name: fcmSlotIndex
fcmSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this slot within the LinkBuilder 3GH chassis.

fcmPortCount.name: fcmPortCount
fcmPortCount.description: The number of FDDI ports present on this board.

fcmBasePortIndex.name: fcmBasePortIndex
fcmBasePortIndex.description: The system-wide index of the first FDDI port on this board. Additional ports on this board will have consecutively increasing port indices following this index.

portTable.name: portTable
portTable.description: A list of port entries. A single instance of this object exists for each port (excluding Ethernet ports) in the LinkBuilder 3GH system. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lb3gh MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available either via the fddiPort group or the enetPort group.

portEntry.name: portEntry
portEntry.description: A port entry contains information common to a particular port located on a particular board within the LinkBuilder 3GH system.

portSlotIndex.name: portSlotIndex
portSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this slot within the LinkBuilder 3GH chassis.

portIndex.name: portIndex
portIndex.description: The index of the port on a particular slot.

portLabel.name: portLabel
portLabel.description: An ASCII text string describing this port.

elmTable.name: elmTable
elmTable.description: A list of Ethernet LAN Module (ELM) entries. An entry exists for each Slot Table Entry whose board type is ELM. This table is indexed by the physical slot number of this ELM within the LinkBuilder 3GH chassis. The entries need not have consecutive slot indices. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lb3gh MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available either via the slot group or the express group.

elmEntry.name: elmEntry
elmEntry.description: An ELM entry contains information common to a single Ethernet LAN Module (ELM) within a LinkBuilder 3GH system.

elmSlotIndex.name: elmSlotIndex
elmSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this slot within the LinkBuilder 3GH chassis.

elmFddiMACCount.name: elmFddiMACCount
elmFddiMACCount.description: The number of FDDI MACs present on this board.

elmBaseFddiMACIndex.name: elmBaseFddiMACIndex
elmBaseFddiMACIndex.description: The system-wide index of the first FDDI MAC on this board. Additional ports on this board will have consecutively increasing port indices following this index.

elmEthernetPortCount.name: elmEthernetPortCount
elmEthernetPortCount.description: The number of Ethernet ports present on this board.

elmBaseEthernetPortIndex.name: elmBaseEthernetPortIndex
elmBaseEthernetPortIndex.description: The system-wide index of the first Ethernet port on this board. Additional ports on this board will have consecutively increasing port indices following this index.

elmAddressThreshold.name: elmAddressThreshold
elmAddressThreshold.description: A reporting threshold for the total number of Ethernet addresses known for this board. When the threshold is reached, the event elmAddress- ThresholdEvent is generated.

elmFddiMACTable.name: elmFddiMACTable
elmFddiMACTable.description: A list of ELM FDDI MAC entries. The entries need not have consecutive slot indices. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lb3gh MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available via the expressFddiPort group.

elmFddiMACEntry.name: elmFddiMACEntry
elmFddiMACEntry.description: An ELM FDDI MAC entry contains information common to an FDDI MAC located on an ELM within a LinkBuilder 3GH system.

elmFddiSlotIndex.name: elmFddiSlotIndex
elmFddiSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this board.

elmFddiMACIndex.name: elmFddiMACIndex
elmFddiMACIndex.description: A unique value for each FDDI MAC on this board.

elmFddiMACForwardedCts.name: elmFddiMACForwardedCts
elmFddiMACForwardedCts.description: A counter indicating the number of frames forwarded by a MAC from an Ethernet port to the FDDI network.

elmFddiMACDroppedCts.name: elmFddiMACDroppedCts
elmFddiMACDroppedCts.description: A counter indicating the number of frames that were dropped by a MAC due to local resource limitation or unknown destination MAC address.

elmEthernetPortTable.name: elmEthernetPortTable
elmEthernetPortTable.description: A list of ELM Ethernet LAN port entries. The slot indices may not be consecutive. The MAC indices must be consecutive. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lb3gh MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available via the expressEthernetPort group.

elmEthernetPortEntry.name: elmEthernetPortEntry
elmEthernetPortEntry.description: An ELM Ethernet LAN port entry contains information common to an Ethernet port located on an Ethernet LAN Module (ELM) within a LinkBuilder 3GH system.

elmEthernetPortSlotIndex.name: elmEthernetPortSlotIndex
elmEthernetPortSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of the slot containing this port within the LinkBuilder 3GH chassis.

elmEthernetPortIndex.name: elmEthernetPortIndex
elmEthernetPortIndex.description: The index of the port on a particular ELM board. This index ranges from 1 to elmEthernetPortCount.

elmEthernetPortLabel.name: elmEthernetPortLabel
elmEthernetPortLabel.description: An ASCII text string describing this Ethernet port.

elmEthernetPortForwardedCts.name: elmEthernetPortForwardedCts
elmEthernetPortForwardedCts.description: A counter indicating the number of frames forwarded from this Ethernet port onto the FDDI network.

elmEthernetPortDroppedCts.name: elmEthernetPortDroppedCts
elmEthernetPortDroppedCts.description: A counter indicating the numer of frames received on this port that were dropped because the destination MAC address was determined to be on the same Ethernet segment as the source MAC address.

elmEthernetPortUTurnCts.name: elmEthernetPortUTurnCts
elmEthernetPortUTurnCts.description: A counter indicating the number of frames received on this Ethernet port and directed to another Ethernet port.

elmEthernetPortState.name: elmEthernetPortState
elmEthernetPortState.description: The state of the Ethernet LAN port. This value can be set to enable or disable the Ethernet LAN port.

elmEthernetPortAction.name: elmEthernetPortAction
elmEthernetPortAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). The result of setting this object to each acceptable value is: freezeAddress: causes all the learned dynamic addresses to be converted into static addresses. flushAddress: causes all the addresses to be flushed from a port's address list. flushDynamicAddress: causes all a port's dynamic addresses to be flushed from the port's address list.

elmEthernetMACAddressTable.name: elmEthernetMACAddressTable
elmEthernetMACAddressTable.description: A list of ELM Ethernet LAN Remote MAC Address entries. The slot indices may not be consecutive. The port indices must be consecutive. Note that this object has been marked as deprecated and is included here for backward compatibilty. It will be removed from the next revision of the lb3gh MIB. The objects defined in this table are now available via the expressEthernetPort group.

elmEthernetMACAddressEntry.name: elmEthernetMACAddressEntry
elmEthernetMACAddressEntry.description: A collection of information describing a remote Ethernet MAC detected to be attached to an Ethernet LAN port.

elmEthernetMACAddressSlotIndex.name: elmEthernetMACAddressSlotIndex
elmEthernetMACAddressSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of the slot containing this ELM within the within th LinkBuilder 3GH chassis.

elmEthernetMACAddressPortIndex.name: elmEthernetMACAddressPortIndex
elmEthernetMACAddressPortIndex.description: The port index of this address entry within the table. This index ranges from 1 to elmEthernetPortCount.

elmEthernetMACAddressIndex.name: elmEthernetMACAddressIndex
elmEthernetMACAddressIndex.description: The index of this address entry within the table.

elmEthernetMACAddressType.name: elmEthernetMACAddressType
elmEthernetMACAddressType.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). Setting this object to invalid (2) removes the corresponding address entry from the table.

elmEthernetMACAddressRemoteAddress.name: elmEthernetMACAddressRemoteAddress
elmEthernetMACAddressRemoteAddress.description: The remote MAC address detected on this Ethernet LAN port.

elmEthernetMACAddressIsStatic.name: elmEthernetMACAddressIsStatic
elmEthernetMACAddressIsStatic.description: A value indicating whether this MAC address was statically configured or dynamically learned on this port.

elmEthernetMACAddressStaticPort.name: elmEthernetMACAddressStaticPort
elmEthernetMACAddressStaticPort.description: If the object elmEthernetMACAddress- IsStatic has value isStatic(1), this object indicates the port for which this MAC address was statically configured.

elmEthernetMACAddressAge.name: elmEthernetMACAddressAge
elmEthernetMACAddressAge.description: This object indicates the time elapsed since this MAC address was added to this port's address table.

lbSystemId.name: lbSystemId
lbSystemId.description: The unique identifier assigned to this system during manufacturing.

lbSystemType.name: lbSystemType
lbSystemType.description: The type of the LinkBuilder system.

lbSystemName.name: lbSystemName
lbSystemName.description: The text string describing this system.

lbSystemManufacturer.name: lbSystemManufacturer
lbSystemManufacturer.description: The text string describing the manufacturer of this system.

lbSystemBackplaneRevision.name: lbSystemBackplaneRevision
lbSystemBackplaneRevision.description: The revision level of the system backplane. Bits 6 and 7 indicate the artwork revision. Bits 0 through 5 indicate the rework level.

lbSystemSlotCount.name: lbSystemSlotCount
lbSystemSlotCount.description: The number of slots in the system.

lbSystemMemorySize.name: lbSystemMemorySize
lbSystemMemorySize.description: The amount of memory (RAM), in bytes, present on the system processor board.

lbSystemFlashMemorySize.name: lbSystemFlashMemorySize
lbSystemFlashMemorySize.description: The amount of flash memory, in bytes, present on the system processor board.

lbSystemNvMemorySize.name: lbSystemNvMemorySize
lbSystemNvMemorySize.description: The amount of non-volatile memory, in bytes, present on the system processor board.

lbSystemSoftwareRevision.name: lbSystemSoftwareRevision
lbSystemSoftwareRevision.description: The revision number of the LinkBuilder system software. Each byte indicates the following: byte 0: major release number. byte 1: minor release number. byte 2: update number. byte 3: bits 7-6: release type. bits 5-0: supplemental identifier.

lbSystemBuildTime.name: lbSystemBuildTime
lbSystemBuildTime.description: The build time of the system software.

lbSystemControlPanelHardwareRevision.name: lbSystemControlPanelHardwareRevision
lbSystemControlPanelHardwareRevision.description: An 8-bit value specifying the revision level of the control panel hardware.

lbSystemControlPanelSoftwareRevision.name: lbSystemControlPanelSoftwareRevision
lbSystemControlPanelSoftwareRevision.description: An 8-bit value specifying the revision level of the control panel software.

lbSystemControlPanelLines.name: lbSystemControlPanelLines
lbSystemControlPanelLines.description: The number of lines in the control panel display.

lbSystemControlPanelColumns.name: lbSystemControlPanelColumns
lbSystemControlPanelColumns.description: The number of columns in the control panel display.

lbSystemControlPanelText.name: lbSystemControlPanelText
lbSystemControlPanelText.description: The currently displayed text in the control panel display.

lbSystemFddiMacCount.name: lbSystemFddiMacCount
lbSystemFddiMacCount.description: The number of FDDI MAC's present in the system.

lbSystemFddiPortCount.name: lbSystemFddiPortCount
lbSystemFddiPortCount.description: The number of FDDI ports present in the system.

lbSystemEthernetPortCount.name: lbSystemEthernetPortCount
lbSystemEthernetPortCount.description: The number of ethernet ports present in the system.

lbSystemExpressFunctionCount.name: lbSystemExpressFunctionCount
lbSystemExpressFunctionCount.description: The number of Ethernet Express functions present in the system. Curently this value is equal to the number of Express boards present in the system.

lbSystemExpressFddiPortCount.name: lbSystemExpressFddiPortCount
lbSystemExpressFddiPortCount.description: The number of Ethernet Express FDDI ports present in the system.

lbSystemExpressEthernetPortCount.name: lbSystemExpressEthernetPortCount
lbSystemExpressEthernetPortCount.description: The number of Ethernet Express ethernet ports present in the system.

lbSystemPowerSupplyCount.name: lbSystemPowerSupplyCount
lbSystemPowerSupplyCount.description: The number of power supply units present in the system.

lbSystemAction.name: lbSystemAction
lbSystemAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). The behavior of setting this object to each of the acceptable values is as follows: reset: resets the LinkBuilder system.

lbSystemBridgeFunctionCount.name: lbSystemBridgeFunctionCount
lbSystemBridgeFunctionCount.description: The number of bridge functions present in the system. Curently this value is equal to the sum of the number of Express and Switching modules in the system.

lbSystemSmtProxyTimeoutBase.name: lbSystemSmtProxyTimeoutBase
lbSystemSmtProxyTimeoutBase.description: The initial timeout value, in seconds, before the SMT proxy attempts to backoff and retry. Since the SMT proxy will attempt three retries before determining that the proxied station is not answering, with the timeout doubling for each retry, the total time for a request to time out is equal to seven times the base timeout value.

lbSystemSmtProxyEvents.name: lbSystemSmtProxyEvents
lbSystemSmtProxyEvents.description: This object determines if the SMT proxy will generate traps for SMT events occuring at other stations. If enabled, the SMT proxy will generate traps for all SMT events, those that occur locally, and those that occur at other stations. If disabled, the SMT proxy will only generate traps for events which occur locally. The default value for this object is enabled(1).

lbSlotTable.name: lbSlotTable
lbSlotTable.description: A list of slot entries. A single instance of this object exists for each slot in the LinkBuilder system.

lbSlotEntry.name: lbSlotEntry
lbSlotEntry.description: A slot entry contains information common to a given slot within a LinkBuilder system.

lbSlotIndex.name: lbSlotIndex
lbSlotIndex.description: The physical slot number of this slot within the system.

lbSlotBoardType.name: lbSlotBoardType
lbSlotBoardType.description: The type of board residing in this slot.

lbSlotBoardRevision.name: lbSlotBoardRevision
lbSlotBoardRevision.description: The revision number of the board in this slot.

lbSlotBoardStatus.name: lbSlotBoardStatus
lbSlotBoardStatus.description: The status of the board in this slot.

lbSlotBoardName.name: lbSlotBoardName
lbSlotBoardName.description: The text string describing this board.

lbSlotBoardNameAbbrev.name: lbSlotBoardNameAbbrev
lbSlotBoardNameAbbrev.description: The abbreviation used to describe this board.

lbSlotFddiMacCount.name: lbSlotFddiMacCount
lbSlotFddiMacCount.description: The number of FDDI MAC's present in this slot.

lbSlotFddiMacBaseIndex.name: lbSlotFddiMacBaseIndex
lbSlotFddiMacBaseIndex.description: The index of the first FDDI MAC in this slot.

lbSlotFddiPortCount.name: lbSlotFddiPortCount
lbSlotFddiPortCount.description: The number of FDDI ports present in this slot.

lbSlotFddiPortBaseIndex.name: lbSlotFddiPortBaseIndex
lbSlotFddiPortBaseIndex.description: The index of the first FDDI port in this slot.

lbSlotEthernetPortCount.name: lbSlotEthernetPortCount
lbSlotEthernetPortCount.description: The number of ethernet ports present in this slot.

lbSlotEthernetPortBaseIndex.name: lbSlotEthernetPortBaseIndex
lbSlotEthernetPortBaseIndex.description: The index of the first ethernet port in this slot.

lbSlotExpressFunctionCount.name: lbSlotExpressFunctionCount
lbSlotExpressFunctionCount.description: The number of Express functions present in this slot.

lbSlotExpressFunctionBaseIndex.name: lbSlotExpressFunctionBaseIndex
lbSlotExpressFunctionBaseIndex.description: The index of the first Express function in this slot.

lbSlotExpressFddiPortCount.name: lbSlotExpressFddiPortCount
lbSlotExpressFddiPortCount.description: The number of Express FDDI ports present in this slot.

lbSlotExpressFddiPortBaseIndex.name: lbSlotExpressFddiPortBaseIndex
lbSlotExpressFddiPortBaseIndex.description: The index of the first Express FDDI port in this slot.

lbSlotExpressEthernetPortCount.name: lbSlotExpressEthernetPortCount
lbSlotExpressEthernetPortCount.description: The number of Express ethernet ports present in this slot.

lbSlotExpressEthernetPortBaseIndex.name: lbSlotExpressEthernetPortBaseIndex
lbSlotExpressEthernetPortBaseIndex.description: The index of the first Express ethernet port in this slot.

lbSlotBoardAction.name: lbSlotBoardAction
lbSlotBoardAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). The behavior of setting this object to each of the acceptable values is as follows: runDiagnostics: runs the board's offline diagnostics.

lbSlotBridgeFunctionCount.name: lbSlotBridgeFunctionCount
lbSlotBridgeFunctionCount.description: The number of bridge functions present in this slot.

lbSlotBridgeFunctionBaseIndex.name: lbSlotBridgeFunctionBaseIndex
lbSlotBridgeFunctionBaseIndex.description: The index of the first bridge function in this slot.

lbFddiMacTable.name: lbFddiMacTable
lbFddiMacTable.description: A list of FDDI MAC entries. A single instance of this object exists for each FDDI MAC present in the system.

lbFddiMacEntry.name: lbFddiMacEntry
lbFddiMacEntry.description: An FDDI MAC entry contains information common to a particular FDDI MAC within the system.

lbFddiMacIndex.name: lbFddiMacIndex
lbFddiMacIndex.description: A unique value for each FDDI MAC in the system. The MAC identified by a particular value of this index is the same MAC as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

lbFddiMacSlotIndex.name: lbFddiMacSlotIndex
lbFddiMacSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this MAC.

lbFddiMacLocalIndex.name: lbFddiMacLocalIndex
lbFddiMacLocalIndex.description: The index of this MAC relative to the slot on which it is physically present.

lbFddiMacByteReceiveRate.name: lbFddiMacByteReceiveRate
lbFddiMacByteReceiveRate.description: The average number of bytes received per second by this MAC during the most recent sampling period.

lbFddiMacPeakByteReceiveRate.name: lbFddiMacPeakByteReceiveRate
lbFddiMacPeakByteReceiveRate.description: The peak value of lbFddiMacByteReceiveRate for this MAC since the system was last initialized.

lbFddiMacFrameReceiveRate.name: lbFddiMacFrameReceiveRate
lbFddiMacFrameReceiveRate.description: The average number of frames received per second by this MAC during the most recent sampling period.

lbFddiMacPeakFrameReceiveRate.name: lbFddiMacPeakFrameReceiveRate
lbFddiMacPeakFrameReceiveRate.description: The peak value of lbFddiMacFrameReceiveRate for this MAC since the system was last initialized.

lbFddiMacByteTransmitRate.name: lbFddiMacByteTransmitRate
lbFddiMacByteTransmitRate.description: The average number of bytes transmitted per second by this MAC during the most recent sampling period.

lbFddiMacPeakByteTransmitRate.name: lbFddiMacPeakByteTransmitRate
lbFddiMacPeakByteTransmitRate.description: The peak value of lbFddiMacByteTransmitRate for this MAC since the system was last initialized.

lbFddiMacFrameTransmitRate.name: lbFddiMacFrameTransmitRate
lbFddiMacFrameTransmitRate.description: The average number of frames transmitted per second by this MAC during the most recent sampling period.

lbFddiMacPeakFrameTransmitRate.name: lbFddiMacPeakFrameTransmitRate
lbFddiMacPeakFrameTransmitRate.description: The peak value of lbFddiMacFrameTransmitRate for this MAC since the system was last initialized.

lbFddiMacReceiveMulticastThreshold.name: lbFddiMacReceiveMulticastThreshold
lbFddiMacReceiveMulticastThreshold.description: The maximum number of multicast frames per second that can be received in the sample interval. The sample interval is one second. The default value for this object is zero which implies an infinite rate.

lbFddiMacBeaconHistory.name: lbFddiMacBeaconHistory
lbFddiMacBeaconHistory.description: This object gives a history of the most recent beacon information received on this MAC. It can contain up to a maximum of eight records. Each record is of the form: source MAC: 6 bytes beacon data length: 2 bytes. beacon data: 0-16 bytes.

lbEthernetPortTable.name: lbEthernetPortTable
lbEthernetPortTable.description: A list of ethernet port entries. A single instance of this object exists for each ethernet port present in the system.

lbEthernetPortEntry.name: lbEthernetPortEntry
lbEthernetPortEntry.description: An ethernet port entry contains information common to a particular ethernet port within the system.

lbEthernetPortIndex.name: lbEthernetPortIndex
lbEthernetPortIndex.description: A unique value for each ethernet port in the system. The port identified by a particular value of this index is the same port as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

lbEthernetPortSlotIndex.name: lbEthernetPortSlotIndex
lbEthernetPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this port.

lbEthernetPortLocalIndex.name: lbEthernetPortLocalIndex
lbEthernetPortLocalIndex.description: The index of this port relative to the slot on which it is physically present.

lbEthernetPortLabel.name: lbEthernetPortLabel
lbEthernetPortLabel.description: An ASCII text string describing this port.

lbEthernetPortChipsetType.name: lbEthernetPortChipsetType
lbEthernetPortChipsetType.description: The type of chipset used to implement this port.

lbEthernetPortLinkStatus.name: lbEthernetPortLinkStatus
lbEthernetPortLinkStatus.description: The current value of the link status for this port.

lbEthernetPortByteReceiveRate.name: lbEthernetPortByteReceiveRate
lbEthernetPortByteReceiveRate.description: The average number of bytes received per second by this port during the most recent sampling period.

lbEthernetPortPeakByteReceiveRate.name: lbEthernetPortPeakByteReceiveRate
lbEthernetPortPeakByteReceiveRate.description: The peak value of lbEthernetPortByteReceiveRate for this port since the system was last initialized.

lbEthernetPortFrameReceiveRate.name: lbEthernetPortFrameReceiveRate
lbEthernetPortFrameReceiveRate.description: The average number of frames received per second by this port during the most recent sampling period.

lbEthernetPortPeakFrameReceiveRate.name: lbEthernetPortPeakFrameReceiveRate
lbEthernetPortPeakFrameReceiveRate.description: The peak value of lbEthernetPortFrameReceiveRate for this port since the system was last initialized.

lbEthernetPortByteTransmitRate.name: lbEthernetPortByteTransmitRate
lbEthernetPortByteTransmitRate.description: The average number of bytes transmitted per second by this port during the most recent sampling period.

lbEthernetPortPeakByteTransmitRate.name: lbEthernetPortPeakByteTransmitRate
lbEthernetPortPeakByteTransmitRate.description: The peak value of lbEthernetPortByteTransmitRate for this port since the system was last initialized.

lbEthernetPortFrameTransmitRate.name: lbEthernetPortFrameTransmitRate
lbEthernetPortFrameTransmitRate.description: The average number of frames transmitted per second by this port during the most recent sampling period.

lbEthernetPortPeakFrameTransmitRate.name: lbEthernetPortPeakFrameTransmitRate
lbEthernetPortPeakFrameTransmitRate.description: The peak value of lbEthernetPortFrameTransmitRate for this port since the system was last initialized.

lbEthernetPortReceiveMulticastThreshold.name: lbEthernetPortReceiveMulticastThreshold
lbEthernetPortReceiveMulticastThreshold.description: The maximum number of multicast frames per second that can be received in the sample interval. The sample interval is one second. The default value for this object is zero which implies an infinite rate.

lbEthernetPortType.name: lbEthernetPortType
lbEthernetPortType.description: Specific description of this port's type.

lbFddiPortTable.name: lbFddiPortTable
lbFddiPortTable.description: A list of FDDI port entries. A single instance of this object exists for each FDDI port in the system.

lbFddiPortEntry.name: lbFddiPortEntry
lbFddiPortEntry.description: A Port entry contains information common to a particular FDDI port in the system.

lbFddiPortIndex.name: lbFddiPortIndex
lbFddiPortIndex.description: A unique value for each FDDI port in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbSystemFddiPortCount.

lbFddiPortSlotIndex.name: lbFddiPortSlotIndex
lbFddiPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this port.

lbFddiPortLocalIndex.name: lbFddiPortLocalIndex
lbFddiPortLocalIndex.description: The index of this port relative to the slot on which it is physically present.

lbFddiPortLabel.name: lbFddiPortLabel
lbFddiPortLabel.description: An ASCII text string describing this port.

lbExpressTable.name: lbExpressTable
lbExpressTable.description: A list of Express function entries.

lbExpressEntry.name: lbExpressEntry
lbExpressEntry.description: An Express entry contains information common to a particular Express function in a given system.

lbExpressIndex.name: lbExpressIndex
lbExpressIndex.description: A unique value for each Express function in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbSystemExpressFunctionCount.

lbExpressSlotIndex.name: lbExpressSlotIndex
lbExpressSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this function.

lbExpressLocalIndex.name: lbExpressLocalIndex
lbExpressLocalIndex.description: The index of this function relative to the slot on which it is physically present.

lbExpressAddressThreshold.name: lbExpressAddressThreshold
lbExpressAddressThreshold.description: A reporting threshold for the total number of Ethernet Addresses known for this board. When this threshold is reached, the event lbEemAddressThresholdEvent is generated.

lbExpressFddiPortTable.name: lbExpressFddiPortTable
lbExpressFddiPortTable.description: A list of Express FDDI port entries.

lbExpressFddiPortEntry.name: lbExpressFddiPortEntry
lbExpressFddiPortEntry.description: A Port entry contains information for a particular Express FDDI port in a given system.

lbExpressFddiPortIndex.name: lbExpressFddiPortIndex
lbExpressFddiPortIndex.description: A unique value for each Express port in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbSystemExpressFddiPortCount.

lbExpressFddiPortSlotIndex.name: lbExpressFddiPortSlotIndex
lbExpressFddiPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this port.

lbExpressFddiPortLocalIndex.name: lbExpressFddiPortLocalIndex
lbExpressFddiPortLocalIndex.description: The index of this port relative to the slot on which it is physically present.

lbExpressFddiPortForwardedCts.name: lbExpressFddiPortForwardedCts
lbExpressFddiPortForwardedCts.description: The number of frames forwarded by this MAC from an ethernet port to the FDDI network.

lbExpressFddiPortDroppedCts.name: lbExpressFddiPortDroppedCts
lbExpressFddiPortDroppedCts.description: The number of frames received by this MAC that were not forwarded.

lbExpressEthernetPortTable.name: lbExpressEthernetPortTable
lbExpressEthernetPortTable.description: A list of Express ethernet port entries.

lbExpressEthernetPortEntry.name: lbExpressEthernetPortEntry
lbExpressEthernetPortEntry.description: An Expres ethernet port entry contains information common to a particular Express ethernet port located in the system.

lbExpressEthernetPortIndex.name: lbExpressEthernetPortIndex
lbExpressEthernetPortIndex.description: A unique value for each Express ethernet port in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbSystemExpressEthernetPortCount.

lbExpressEthernetPortSlotIndex.name: lbExpressEthernetPortSlotIndex
lbExpressEthernetPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this port.

lbExpressEthernetPortLocalIndex.name: lbExpressEthernetPortLocalIndex
lbExpressEthernetPortLocalIndex.description: The index of this port relative to the slot on which it is physically present.

lbExpressEthernetPortForwardedCts.name: lbExpressEthernetPortForwardedCts
lbExpressEthernetPortForwardedCts.description: The number of frames forwarded from this ethernet port to the FDDI network.

lbExpressEthernetPortDroppedCts.name: lbExpressEthernetPortDroppedCts
lbExpressEthernetPortDroppedCts.description: The number of frames received by this ethernet port that were not forwarded or u-turned.

lbExpressEthernetPortUTurnCts.name: lbExpressEthernetPortUTurnCts
lbExpressEthernetPortUTurnCts.description: The number of frames received by this ethernet port that were directed to another ethernet port.

lbExpressEthernetPortAction.name: lbExpressEthernetPortAction
lbExpressEthernetPortAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). The behavior of setting this object to each of the acceptable values is as follows: freezeAddress: causes all the learned dynamic addresses to be converted into static addresses. flushAddress: causes all the addresses to be flushed from a port's address list. flushDynamicAddress: causes all the port's dynamic addresses to be flushed from a port's address list.

lbExpressEthernetPortAddressTable.name: lbExpressEthernetPortAddressTable
lbExpressEthernetPortAddressTable.description: A list of Express Remote MAC Address entries.

lbExpressEthernetPortAddressEntry.name: lbExpressEthernetPortAddressEntry
lbExpressEthernetPortAddressEntry.description: An entry contains information describing a remote Ethernet MAC detected to be attached to an Express port.

lbExpressEthernetPortAddressPortIndex.name: lbExpressEthernetPortAddressPortIndex
lbExpressEthernetPortAddressPortIndex.description: A unique value for each Express ethernet port in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbSystemExpressEthernetPortCount.

lbExpressEthernetPortAddressIndex.name: lbExpressEthernetPortAddressIndex
lbExpressEthernetPortAddressIndex.description: The index of this address entry within the address table.

lbExpressEthernetPortAddressSlotIndex.name: lbExpressEthernetPortAddressSlotIndex
lbExpressEthernetPortAddressSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this port.

lbExpressEthernetPortAddressType.name: lbExpressEthernetPortAddressType
lbExpressEthernetPortAddressType.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). Setting this object to invalid (2) will remove the corresponding address entry from the table.

lbExpressEthernetPortAddressRemoteAddres.name: lbExpressEthernetPortAddressRemoteAddress
lbExpressEthernetPortAddressRemoteAddres.description: The remote MAC address detected on this port.

lbExpressEthernetPortAddressIsStatic.name: lbExpressEthernetPortAddressIsStatic
lbExpressEthernetPortAddressIsStatic.description: A value indicating whether this MAC address was statically configured or was dynamically learned on this port.

lbExpressEthernetPortAddressStaticPort.name: lbExpressEthernetPortAddressStaticPort
lbExpressEthernetPortAddressStaticPort.description: If the object lbExpressEthernetPortAddressIsStatic has value isStatic(1), this object indicates the port for which this MAC address was statically configured.

lbExpressEthernetPortAddressAge.name: lbExpressEthernetPortAddressAge
lbExpressEthernetPortAddressAge.description: This object indicates the time, in seconds, elapsed since this MAC address was added to this port's address table.

lbPowerSupplyTable.name: lbPowerSupplyTable
lbPowerSupplyTable.description: A list of power supply entries.

lbPowerSupplyEntry.name: lbPowerSupplyEntry
lbPowerSupplyEntry.description: A power supply entry contains information common for a particular power supply unit in the system.

lbPowerSupplyIndex.name: lbPowerSupplyIndex
lbPowerSupplyIndex.description: A unique value for each power supply in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbSystemPowerSupplyCount.

lbPowerSupplyLocation.name: lbPowerSupplyLocation
lbPowerSupplyLocation.description: The physical slot in which this power supply unit resides in the system.

lbPowerSupplyStatus.name: lbPowerSupplyStatus
lbPowerSupplyStatus.description: The status of the power supply. A value of 0 indicates a working unit. A non-zero value represents a bit mask of the possible failure types. Each set bit indicates the following failure type: bit0: systemAcFailure bit1: systemPlus5Failure bit2: systemPlus12Failure bit3: systemOverTemperatureFailure.

lbPowerSupplyFailureType.name: lbPowerSupplyFailureType
lbPowerSupplyFailureType.description: This object is sent in the varlist when the lbPowerSupplyFailureEvent trap is generated. It indicates the particular failure type that caused this trap to be generated.

lbPowerSupplyLastFailure.name: lbPowerSupplyLastFailure
lbPowerSupplyLastFailure.description: This object represents the most recent power supply failure type. If no failure has occured, the value of this object is none. This object is included in the varlist when the lbPowerSupplyFailureEvent trap is generated. It indicates the failure type that caused the trap to be generated.

lbBridgeTable.name: lbBridgeTable
lbBridgeTable.description: A list of bridge function entries.

lbBridgeEntry.name: lbBridgeEntry
lbBridgeEntry.description: A bridge entry contains information common to a particular bridge function in a given system.

lbBridgeIndex.name: lbBridgeIndex
lbBridgeIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge function in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbSystemBridgeFunctionCount.

lbBridgeBaseSlotIndex.name: lbBridgeBaseSlotIndex
lbBridgeBaseSlotIndex.description: The slot number of the lowest numbered slot which contains a physical port that this bridge function controls.

lbBridgePortCount.name: lbBridgePortCount
lbBridgePortCount.description: The number of ports that this bridge function controls.

lbBridgeAddressTableSize.name: lbBridgeAddressTableSize
lbBridgeAddressTableSize.description: The size of the address table for this bridge function.

lbBridgeAddressThreshold.name: lbBridgeAddressThreshold
lbBridgeAddressThreshold.description: A reporting threshold for the total number of addresses known for this board. When this threshold is reached, the event lbBridgeAddressThresholdEvent is generated. The range of valid values for setting this object is between 1 and the value reported by lbBridgeAddressTableSize + 1 (Note that this range applies to values issued in set requests. The current value may be outside this range, for example if the value of lbBridgeMode is changed). Setting this object to one greater than the address table size disables the generation of lbBridgeAddressThresholdEvents since the limit will never be reached.

lbBridgeMode.name: lbBridgeMode
lbBridgeMode.description: The operational mode of this bridge function. Note that bridges which report notSupported(3) will not support sets of this object, and that the value notSupported(3) is not a valid value for a set operation.

lbBridgeLocalIndex.name: lbBridgeLocalIndex
lbBridgeLocalIndex.description: The index of this bridge function relative to the slot on which it is physically present.

lbBridgePortTable.name: lbBridgePortTable
lbBridgePortTable.description: A list of bridge port entries.

lbBridgePortEntry.name: lbBridgePortEntry
lbBridgePortEntry.description: A Port entry contains information for a particular bridge port in a given system.

lbBridgePortBridgeIndex.name: lbBridgePortBridgeIndex
lbBridgePortBridgeIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge function in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbSystemBridgeFunctionCount.

lbBridgePortIndex.name: lbBridgePortIndex
lbBridgePortIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge port controlled by a given bridge function. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbBridgePortCount for the bridge function which this entry references.

lbBridgePortSlotIndex.name: lbBridgePortSlotIndex
lbBridgePortSlotIndex.description: The slot number corresponding to the physical location of this port.

lbBridgePortLocalIndex.name: lbBridgePortLocalIndex
lbBridgePortLocalIndex.description: The index of this port relative to the slot on which it is physically present and its port type. For example FDDI ports in a slot are identified with local indices from 1 to the number of FDDI ports in that slot, and the Ethernet ports in the same slot are identified with local indices from 1 to the number of Ethernet ports in that slot.

lbBridgePortIpFragmentationEnabled.name: lbBridgePortIpFragmentationEnabled
lbBridgePortIpFragmentationEnabled.description: A flag indicating whether or not IP fragmentation is enabled on this bridge port. Note that bridges which report notSupported(3) will not support sets of this object, and that the value notSupported(3) is not a valid value for a set operation.

lbBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit.name: lbBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit
lbBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit.description: The maximum number of multicast frames per second that can be received in the sample interval. The sample interval is four seconds. The default value for this object is zero which implies an infinite rate.

lbBridgePortAddressAction.name: lbBridgePortAddressAction
lbBridgePortAddressAction.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). The behavior of setting this object to each of the acceptable values is as follows: freezeAddress: causes all the learned dynamic addresses to be converted into static addresses. flushAddress: causes all the addresses to be flushed from the port's address list. flushDynamicAddress: causes all dynamic addresses to be flushed from the port's address list.

lbBridgePortTotalForwardedCts.name: lbBridgePortTotalForwardedCts
lbBridgePortTotalForwardedCts.description: The total number of frames forwarded from this port to all other ports of this bridge. Note that the total forwarded count is NOT equal to the receive count minus the discard count, as a single received multicast/broadcast frame can be forwarded to multiple bridge ports. Also frames which are 'flooded' because of unknown destination addresses account for multiple forwarding as well. The total forwarding count is the instantaneous sumation of the 'forwarded to' counts to all other ports of the bridge.

lbBridgePortManagementFramesReceived.name: lbBridgePortManagementFramesReceived
lbBridgePortManagementFramesReceived.description: The number of bridge management frames received by this port.

lbBridgePortTotalDiscards.name: lbBridgePortTotalDiscards
lbBridgePortTotalDiscards.description: The total number of frames discarded by this port.

lbBridgePortReceiveBlockedDiscards.name: lbBridgePortReceiveBlockedDiscards
lbBridgePortReceiveBlockedDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port because the the receiving bridge port was not in the 'forwarding' state.

lbBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExceede.name: lbBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExceededs
lbBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExceede.description: The number of multicast/broadcast frames discarded by this port because the lbBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit was exceeded.

lbBridgePortReceiveSecurityDiscards.name: lbBridgePortReceiveSecurityDiscards
lbBridgePortReceiveSecurityDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port because they contained source addresses which were statically configured on another bridge port. A statically configured address (station), which is not allowed to move, appears to have moved.

lbBridgePortReceiveUnknownDiscards.name: lbBridgePortReceiveUnknownDiscards
lbBridgePortReceiveUnknownDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port because the destination address was unknown. Note that this counter is only valid for FDDI ports, and only when the bridge is an EEM, or an ESM operating in express mode.

lbBridgePortReceiveOtherDiscards.name: lbBridgePortReceiveOtherDiscards
lbBridgePortReceiveOtherDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port because they contained either invalid (group) source addresses or source addresses belonging to this bridge (indicative of network loops).

lbBridgePortReceiveErrorDiscards.name: lbBridgePortReceiveErrorDiscards
lbBridgePortReceiveErrorDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port because of internal bridge system errors (e.g., hardware and software address table discrepencies).

lbBridgePortSameSegmentDiscards.name: lbBridgePortSameSegmentDiscards
lbBridgePortSameSegmentDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port because the destination address is known on the same network segment as the source address, i.e., the frame does not need to be bridged.

lbBridgePortTransmitBlockedDiscards.name: lbBridgePortTransmitBlockedDiscards
lbBridgePortTransmitBlockedDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port because the the transmitting bridge port was not in the 'forwarding' state.

lbBridgePortTotalFiltered.name: lbBridgePortTotalFiltered
lbBridgePortTotalFiltered.description: The total number of frames discarded by this port due to user defined filters.

lbBridgePortReceiveUnicastFiltered.name: lbBridgePortReceiveUnicastFiltered
lbBridgePortReceiveUnicastFiltered.description: The number of frames discarded by this port due to user defined receive path filters.

lbBridgePortReceiveMulticastFiltered.name: lbBridgePortReceiveMulticastFiltered
lbBridgePortReceiveMulticastFiltered.description: The number of frames discarded by this port due to user defined receive multicast path filters.

lbBridgePortTransmitUnicastFiltered.name: lbBridgePortTransmitUnicastFiltered
lbBridgePortTransmitUnicastFiltered.description: The number of frames discarded by this port due to user defined transmit path filters.

lbBridgePortTransmitMulticastFiltered.name: lbBridgePortTransmitMulticastFiltered
lbBridgePortTransmitMulticastFiltered.description: The number of frames discarded by this port due to user defined transmit multicast path filters.

lbBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExceede.name: lbBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExceededCount
lbBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimitExceede.description: The number of times the lbBridgePortReceiveMulticastLimit was exceeded.

lbBridgePortForwardedToTable.name: lbBridgePortForwardedToTable
lbBridgePortForwardedToTable.description: A list of port forwarding count information.

lbBridgePortForwardedToEntry.name: lbBridgePortForwardedToEntry
lbBridgePortForwardedToEntry.description: A bridge port forwarded-to entry contains information on the count of frames forwarded from the receiving port indicated by the corresponding lbBridgePortForwardedToReceivePortIndex, to the destination port indicated by the corresponding lbBridgePortForwardedToDstPortIndex. Note that no entries exist which are indexed with the same values for both the lbBridgePortForwardedToReceivePortIndex and the lbBridgePortForwardedToDstPortIndex objects.

lbBridgePortForwardedToBridgeIndex.name: lbBridgePortForwardedToBridgeIndex
lbBridgePortForwardedToBridgeIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge function in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbSystemBridgeFunctionCount.

lbBridgePortForwardedToReceivePortIndex.name: lbBridgePortForwardedToReceivePortIndex
lbBridgePortForwardedToReceivePortIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge port controlled by a given bridge function. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbBridgePortCount for the bridge function which this entry references. This port index refers to the receiving port which is forwarding frames.

lbBridgePortForwardedToDstPortIndex.name: lbBridgePortForwardedToDstPortIndex
lbBridgePortForwardedToDstPortIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge port controlled by a given bridge function. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbBridgePortCount for the bridge function which this entry references. This port index refers to the destination port to which frames are being forwarded.

lbBridgePortForwardedToCount.name: lbBridgePortForwardedToCount
lbBridgePortForwardedToCount.description: The count of frames forwarded from the receiving port to the destination port.

lbBridgePortFilteredToTable.name: lbBridgePortFilteredToTable
lbBridgePortFilteredToTable.description: A list of port filtering count information.

lbBridgePortFilteredToEntry.name: lbBridgePortFilteredToEntry
lbBridgePortFilteredToEntry.description: A bridge port filtered-to entry contains information on the count of frames filtered from the receiving port indicated by the corresponding lbBridgePortFilteredToReceivePortIndex, to the destination port indicated by the corresponding lbBridgePortFilteredToDstPortIndex. Note that no entries exist which are indexed with the same values for both the lbBridgePortFilteredToReceivePortIndex and the lbBridgePortFilteredToDstPortIndex objects.

lbBridgePortFilteredToBridgeIndex.name: lbBridgePortFilteredToBridgeIndex
lbBridgePortFilteredToBridgeIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge function in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbSystemBridgeFunctionCount.

lbBridgePortFilteredToReceivePortIndex.name: lbBridgePortFilteredToReceivePortIndex
lbBridgePortFilteredToReceivePortIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge port controlled by a given bridge function. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbBridgePortCount for the bridge function which this entry references. This port index refers to the receiving port which is filtering frames.

lbBridgePortFilteredToDstPortIndex.name: lbBridgePortFilteredToDstPortIndex
lbBridgePortFilteredToDstPortIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge port controlled by a given bridge function. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbBridgePortCount for the bridge function which this entry references. This port index refers to the destination port to which frames are being filtered.

lbBridgePortFilteredToCount.name: lbBridgePortFilteredToCount
lbBridgePortFilteredToCount.description: The count of frames filtered from the receiving port to the destination port.

lbBridgePortAddressTable.name: lbBridgePortAddressTable
lbBridgePortAddressTable.description: A list of bridge port address entries.

lbBridgePortAddressEntry.name: lbBridgePortAddressEntry
lbBridgePortAddressEntry.description: An bridge port address entry contains information about particular bridge port address in a given system.

lbBridgePortAddressBridgeIndex.name: lbBridgePortAddressBridgeIndex
lbBridgePortAddressBridgeIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge function in the system. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbSystemBridgeFunctionCount.

lbBridgePortAddressPortIndex.name: lbBridgePortAddressPortIndex
lbBridgePortAddressPortIndex.description: A unique value for each bridge port controlled by a given bridge function. It's value ranges between 1 and the value of lbBridgePortCount for the bridge function which this entry references.

lbBridgePortAddressIndex.name: lbBridgePortAddressIndex
lbBridgePortAddressIndex.description: The index of this address entry within the bridge address table.

lbBridgePortAddressRemoteAddress.name: lbBridgePortAddressRemoteAddress
lbBridgePortAddressRemoteAddress.description: The remote MAC address detected on the port corresponding to this entry. Setting this object attempts to create a new entry in the table. Since the value of lbBridgePortAddressIndex is determined automatically internal to the bridge, a set is only successful if the index value specified for lbBridgePortAddressIndex is zero. A get-next using the values of lbBridgePortAddressBridgeIndex and lbBridgePortAddressPortIndex can be used to determine the address index assigned to the newly added address entry.

lbBridgePortAddressType.name: lbBridgePortAddressType
lbBridgePortAddressType.description: This object, when read, always returns the value other (1). Setting this object to invalid (2) will remove the corresponding address entry from the table.

lbBridgePortAddressIsStatic.name: lbBridgePortAddressIsStatic
lbBridgePortAddressIsStatic.description: A value indicating whether this MAC address was statically configured or was dynamically learned.

lbBridgePortAddressStaticPort.name: lbBridgePortAddressStaticPort
lbBridgePortAddressStaticPort.description: If the object lbBridgePortAddressIsStatic has value isStatic(1), this object indicates the local port index (as reported by lbBridgePortLocalIndex) for which this MAC address was statically configured. If the object lbBridgePortAddressIsStatic has the value isDynamic(2), the value of this object is 0.

lbBridgePortAddressAge.name: lbBridgePortAddressAge
lbBridgePortAddressAge.description: This object indicates the time, in seconds, elapsed since a packet containing this address as a source was last seen on the port corresponding to this entry.

lbTrapEnterpriseTable.name: lbTrapEnterpriseTable
lbTrapEnterpriseTable.description: This table contains a listing of enterprises under which various traps are defined. In all cases except for the MIB-II generic traps, the enterprise under which a trap is defined is the same as that appearing in the ENTERPRISE portion of the trap. Associated with each trap enterprise is a trap enterprise index.

lbTrapEnterpriseTableEntry.name: lbTrapEnterpriseTableEntry
lbTrapEnterpriseTableEntry.description: Information relating a specific trap enterprise OID with a trap enterprise index.

lbTrapEnterpriseIndex.name: lbTrapEnterpriseIndex
lbTrapEnterpriseIndex.description: A unique index corresponding to a particular enterprise OID under which traps are defined. This value of this object corresponding to a particular enterprise OID will remain constant accross system resets.

lbTrapEnterpriseOID.name: lbTrapEnterpriseOID
lbTrapEnterpriseOID.description: An enterpise OID under which traps are defined.

lbTrapDestTable.name: lbTrapDestTable
lbTrapDestTable.description: This table contains information specifying which traps will be transmitted by the LANplex to a given destination address. The table is indexed by the destination address, the index of the enterprise which generates the trap, and the trap number. Each entry in the table with a status of valid identifies a trap which, when generated, will be transmitted to the corresponding destination address listed in that entry.

lbTrapDestTableEntry.name: lbTrapDestTableEntry
lbTrapDestTableEntry.description: Information relating a trap with a destination address to which the trap will be sent when it is generated.

lbTrapDestAddr.name: lbTrapDestAddr
lbTrapDestAddr.description: The network address to which the trap identified by this entry is to be transmitted.

lbTrapDestEnterpriseIndex.name: lbTrapDestEnterpriseIndex
lbTrapDestEnterpriseIndex.description: The enterprise index of the enterprise identified in this entry. The value of this object is the same as the lbTrapEnterpriseIndex value for a given enterprise.

lbTrapNumber.name: lbTrapNumber
lbTrapNumber.description: The number of the trap within the corresponding enterprise for this entry.

lbTrapEntryStatus.name: lbTrapEntryStatus
lbTrapEntryStatus.description: The status of the trap destination table entry. Setting this object to valid has the effect of attempting to add the row corresponding to the instance specified. If the instance already exists, the set is successful (with no new entry added). If the instance specified is invalid, the set fails, otherwise the set succeeds and results in a new entry being added to the table. Setting this object to invalid has the effect of removing the corresponding entry from the table.

lbSlotInsertEvent.name: lbSlotInsertEvent
lbSlotInsertEvent.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a board is inserted into a particular slot in the chassis.

lbSlotExtractEvent.name: lbSlotExtractEvent
lbSlotExtractEvent.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a board is extracted from a particular slot in the chassis.

lbBridgeAddressThresholdEvent.name: lbBridgeAddressThresholdEvent
lbBridgeAddressThresholdEvent.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the number of addresses stored in the bridge reaches lbBridgeAddressThreshold.

lbSystemOverTemperatureEvent.name: lbSystemOverTemperatureEvent
lbSystemOverTemperatureEvent.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the system temperature exceeds a certain threshold.

lbSlotOverTemperatureEvent.name: lbSlotOverTemperatureEvent
lbSlotOverTemperatureEvent.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the temperature of a board in a particular slot exceeds a certain threshold.

lbPowerSupplyFailureEvent.name: lbPowerSupplyFailureEvent
lbPowerSupplyFailureEvent.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a power supply unit fails in the system.
